reMarkable Connection Utility (RCU)
===================================
RCU is a desktop client for all-in-one offline management of reMarkable
e-paper tablet(s). Users may create and restore full backups, take
screenshots, and manage notebooks, templates, wallpaper, and third-party
software. It ensures the user's data is completely in their control,
unshackled from the manufacturer's proprietary cloud service.

RCU is licensed under the GNU AGPLv3 (or later).

The RCU User Manual is the primary source of documentation. All the 
files in the manual/ directory, and the text itself, are CC-BY-SA 4.0.

reMarkable(R) is a registered tradebark of reMarkable AS. RCU is not 
affiliated with, or endorsed by, reMarkable AS. The use of “reMarkable” 
in this work refers to the company’s e-paper tablet products.


Building Documetation
=====================
The entire project documentation can be found in manual/manual.tex. You
can generate the manual/manual.pdf file by running `make doc`.


